[2026-03-18T16:15:42Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EMDA3AVN912dGvXueWfDW2","type":"tool_result","content":"   340→`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n   341→rejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n   342→\n   343→**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer —\n   344→parse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\n   345→back. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n   346→\n   347→Branches B and C often fire together — a new script step needs both the script\n   348→file (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n   349→\n   350→### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n   351→\n   352→After all changes are applied:\n   353→\n   354→1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   355→   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   356→2. **Restore** — restores a file from a named snapshot (used by the Curator\n   357→   to roll back corrupted writes)\n   358→3. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   359→   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n   360→4. **Knowledge base update** — merges the Reflector's lessons into\n   361→   `knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl` with ID-based deduplication and optional\n   362→   pruning via `MaxPromptBullets`\n   363→\n   364→## Knowledge Base Structure\n   365→\n   366→The knowledge base is a JSONL file — one JSON object per line, each\n   367→representing a `Lesson`. Lessons are keyed by `id` for deduplication: if a\n   368→lesson with the same ID already exists, it is updated in place rather than\n   369→appended. When `MaxPromptBullets` is configured and the total number of\n   370→lessons exceeds that limit, the oldest entries are pruned to stay within\n   371→bounds.\n   372→\n   373→```jsonl\n   374→{\"id\":\"P001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add sanitization rule to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   375→{\"id\":\"W001\",\"category\":\"new_step\",\"step_type\":\"script\",\"insight\":\"Added gosec security scan step\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add gosec step to workflow\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n   376→{\"id\":\"F001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Test timeout failures correlate with database connection setup\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add retry guidance to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-ghi\",\"run-jkl\"],\"confidence\":\"medium\"}\n   377→```\n   378→\n   379→The structured JSONL format enables reliable deduplication by lesson ID and\n   380→programmatic querying. Lessons that are superseded by newer insights with the\n   381→same ID are replaced automatically.\n   382→\n   383→## Trigger Logic\n   384→\n   385→### When Evolution Runs\n   386→\n   387→The pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\n   388→or failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n   389→\n   390→- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n   391→  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n   392→  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n   393→- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n   394→  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n   395→- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n   396→  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n   397→  the executor branches.\n   398→\n   399→### History Window"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fa9a8c88-04cf-4eb4-ae7d-479d0dedfad3","uuid":"d1bd0e90-b70f-4a2c-96c3-092f28f433f0","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:15:34.864Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\nrejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n\n**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer —\nparse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\nback. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n\nBranches B and C often fire together — a new script step needs both the script\nfile (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n\n### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n\nAfter all changes are applied:\n\n1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n2. **Restore** — restores a file from a named snapshot (used by the Curator\n   to roll back corrupted writes)\n3. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n4. **Knowledge base update** — merges the Reflector's lessons into\n   `knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl` with ID-based deduplication and optional\n   pruning via `MaxPromptBullets`\n\n## Knowledge Base Structure\n\nThe knowledge base is a JSONL file — one JSON object per line, each\nrepresenting a `Lesson`. Lessons are keyed by `id` for deduplication: if a\nlesson with the same ID already exists, it is updated in place rather than\nappended. When `MaxPromptBullets` is configured and the total number of\nlessons exceeds that limit, the oldest entries are pruned to stay within\nbounds.\n\n```jsonl\n{\"id\":\"P001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add sanitization rule to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n{\"id\":\"W001\",\"category\":\"new_step\",\"step_type\":\"script\",\"insight\":\"Added gosec security scan step\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add gosec step to workflow\",\"evidence\":[\"run-abc\",\"run-def\"],\"confidence\":\"high\"}\n{\"id\":\"F001\",\"category\":\"prompt_improvement\",\"insight\":\"Test timeout failures correlate with database connection setup\",\"suggested_action\":\"Add retry guidance to prompt\",\"evidence\":[\"run-ghi\",\"run-jkl\"],\"confidence\":\"medium\"}\n```\n\nThe structured JSONL format enables reliable deduplication by lesson ID and\nprogrammatic querying. Lessons that are superseded by newer insights with the\nsame ID are replaced automatically.\n\n## Trigger Logic\n\n### When Evolution Runs\n\nThe pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\nor failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n\n- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n  the executor branches.\n\n### History Window","numLines":60,"startLine":340,"totalLines":528}}}
